- "Genre of content" refers to categories like academic, fiction, etc.;
- "Pronouns" are words used to replace nouns, such as "I," "you," "he/she/it/they."

- Subjective case pronouns are used as the subject of a sentence (e.g., I, you, he, she, it, they);
- Objective case pronouns are used as the object of a sentence or preposition (e.g., me, you, him, her, it, them);
- Formality in language refers to the level of politeness or formality in speech or writing.

sql:
SELECT AVG(pu.usage_count) AS average_usage_count
FROM pronoun_usage pu
JOIN pronouns p ON pu.pronoun_id = p.pronoun_id;

